    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-10-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="185" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d185">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 185.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Fish</persName> to <persName type="to">Baron
                                Gerolt</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 22, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, Secretary of State of the United States, has the honor
                            to acknowledge the receipt of the communication addressed to him on the
                            15th instant by Baron Gerolt, the envoy extraordinary and minister
                            plenipotentiary of the North German Union, relating to the complaints
                            made by the governments of North Germany and France as to alleged
                            violations of international law in their respective military
                            operations.</p>
                <p>The undersigned avails himself of this opportunity to renew to Baron
                            Gerolt the assurance of his highest consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
